Definition: Logical model describing the model for the prescription laboratory. This draft is used in the HL7 Belgian workgroup for laboratory.

Short: The NIHDI of the prescribing healthcare party
Definition: The NIHDI of the prescribing healthcare party

Short: NIHDI of co prescriber substitute party
Definition: NIHDI of co prescriber substitute party

Short: Status of co prescribing status (to sign, signed or refused)
Definition: Status of co prescribing status (to sign, signed or refused)

Short: The SSIN of the person for which the laboratory is prescribed.
Definition: The SSIN of the person for which the laboratory is prescribed.

Short: A reference to the provider party (e.g. a NIHDI number for a healthcare professional, a SSIN or only a displaystring for a non professional caregiver,...)
Definition: A reference to the provider party (e.g. a NIHDI number for a healthcare professional, a SSIN or only a displaystring for a non professional caregiver,...)

Short: Required discipline of the provider party
Definition: Required discipline of the provider party

Short: Reference ID of the UHMEP once availaboratoryle there
Definition: Reference ID of the UHMEP once availaboratoryle there

Short: When this prescription is executed, availaboratoryle after start of execution
Definition: When this prescription is executed, availaboratoryle after start of execution

Short: Parties that shall be informed of the results of the prescription other then the prescriber.
Definition: Parties that shall be informed of the results of the prescription other then the prescriber.
